    <aside id=3D"about" class=3D"info" style=3D"display: none;">
      <h2>What Is This?</h2>

      <p>
        This is a tool for reading <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/International_Phonetic_Alphabet" target=3D"_blank">International Phonetic =
Alphabet (IPA)</a> notation aloud.
      </p>

      <p>
        It makes it easy to actually hear how words are pronounced based on=
 their phonetic spelling, without
        having to look up each character in <a href=3D"https://upload.wikim=
edia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/8e/IPA_chart_2018.pdf" target=3D"_blank">the I=
PA chart</a> and string the sounds together yourself.
      </p>

      <p>
        For example, "budgerigar" (AKA the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Budgerigar" target=3D"_blank">common parakeet</a>) can be pronounc=
ed according to its IPA notation
        <code>/=CB=88b=CA=8Cd=CA=92=C9=99r=C9=AA=C9=A1=C9=91=CB=90r/</code>=
.
      </p>

      <h2>How Do You Use It?</h2>

      <p>
        Find a word you would like to hear pronounced, grab the IPA notatio=
n (if you don't already have it,
        <a href=3D"https://en.wiktionary.org/" target=3D"_blank">Wiktionary=
</a> is a great place to look),
        toss it in the form, and hit the "Read" button.
      </p>

      <p>
        For example, <code>/=CB=88p=C9=AAd=CA=92=C9=99n/</code> will be rea=
d as "pigeon."
      </p>

      <h2>How Does It Work?</h2>

      <p>
        I had fun making this, so I wrote about how it was built <a href=3D=
"https://cuttlesoft.com/blog/2018/09/13/pronouncing-things-with-amazons-pol=
ly/" target=3D"_blank">here</a>!
      </p>

      <p>
        Basically, the current version structures a request to Amazon Polly=
,
        a text-to-speech service, then retrieves and plays the resulting ge=
nerated audio.
      </p>
      <p>
        (This also means that pronunciation is constrained by which phoneme=
s Polly does or does not support;
        details about specific phonemes can be found in their
        <a href=3D"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/polly/latest/dg/ref-phoneme-=
tables-shell.html" target=3D"_blank">documentation of supported phonemes</a=
>.)
      </p>

      <h2>Who Am I?</h2>

      <p>
        I'm nobody! Who are you?

